---
/* /eat methodology footer (BUILD_SPEC §6). Plain prose, no callout box.
   Copy is verbatim from the spec and pre-approved — do not rewrite. */
---

<section class="emethod">
  <div class="emethod-wrap">
    <h2 class="emethod-h">About this list</h2>
    <p>
      282 restaurants from Tabelog's Hyakumeiten lists — 2024, 2025, and 2026
      selections across 13 cuisine categories plus the shokudo (small-eatery)
      list. Tabelog's Hyakumeiten are voted by Japanese diners; each list is
      the top 100 in that category for the year. We aggregate. We don't review.
    </p>
    <p>
      Tabelog publishes one Hyakumeiten list per cuisine, not a single
      cross-genre "top 100." There's no "best of best." The closest is the
      Shokudo Hyakumeiten, which ranks the top 100 small everyday eateries
      nationwide — that's the Shokudo chip on this page.
    </p>
    <p>
      What's missing: individual restaurant pages on Tabelog, current
      open/closed status, and detailed addresses are not in this build. Use
      the Google Maps link on each card for those. Some restaurants may have
      closed since the list was published; we'll prune as that becomes known.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .emethod {
    background: var(--color-white);
    padding: 8px 0 56px;
  }
  .emethod-wrap {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--gutter-mobile);
  }
  .emethod-h {
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .emethod p {
    max-width: 64ch;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-60);
  }
  .emethod p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .emethod {
      padding: 16px 0 72px;
    }
    .emethod-wrap {
      padding: 0 var(--gutter-desktop);
    }
    .emethod-h {
      font-size: 24px;
    }
    .emethod p {
      font-size: 15px;
    }
  }
</style>
